cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper uses data from location-sharing services and social media platforms to analyze human behavior and emotions in urban areas. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper also touches upon topics related to urban planning, land use, and human mobility patterns.
